 	<li>Ensure the vehicle is operating correctly and there is no fluid leakage. • If an alarm system is present, deactivate it.</li>
 	<li>Before conveying a vehicle, it must be photographed from all angles to establish its condition.</li>
 	<li>Ensure you have all necessary documentation, including the title and registration for the vehicle.</li>
 	<li>Notify the transportation company if the vehicle is inoperable for they to make the necessary arrangements.</li>
 	<li>If you transport your vehicle to Alaska or Hawaii with more than a quarter tank of fuel, additional degassing fees will apply.</li>
</ul>
